WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.800
We grow enough food to feed 10 billion people.
800 million go hungry.

00:00:07.800 --> 00:00:14.400
This is not a scarcity problem.
This is a software bug in civilization.

00:00:14.400 --> 00:00:16.400
Layer 1. Local growing.

00:00:16.400 --> 00:00:25.200
Vertical farms in every city.
95% less water, zero transport, year-round harvest.

00:00:25.200 --> 00:00:27.200
Layer 2. AI distribution.

00:00:27.200 --> 00:00:38.200
Food moves based on what neighborhoods need,
not what stores ordered six days ago.
Perishables rerouted in real time before they spoil.

00:00:38.200 --> 00:00:40.200
Layer 3. Personalized nutrition.

00:00:40.200 --> 00:00:48.200
Your body tells you what it needs.
Your food meets you where you are —
your culture, your biology, your life stage.

00:00:48.200 --> 00:00:49.200
Layer 4. Waste dies.

00:00:49.200 --> 00:00:58.200
Ugly produce gets processed.
Scraps feed the farm.
The loop closes.

00:00:58.200 --> 00:00:59.200
Layer 5.

00:00:59.200 --> 00:01:05.200
Nutrition becomes infrastructure.
Not a luxury. Not a market. A right.

00:01:05.200 --> 00:01:13.200
Like roads. Like water.
Fund the food — or keep funding the hospitals.
Your call.

00:01:13.200 --> 00:01:22.200
Four corporations own 60% of the world's seeds.
They patented your food and sold it back to you
with a prescription for their poison.

00:01:22.200 --> 00:01:28.760
But open-source seeds can't be repatented.
Once freed, freed forever.

00:01:28.760 --> 00:01:33.280
The revolution won't be patented.
It'll be planted.

00:01:33.280 --> 00:01:39.240
This isn't utopia. It's logistics.
Every piece of this exists right now.

00:01:39.240 --> 00:01:48.440
The technology is here. The food is here.
The only thing missing is the coordination layer.
And that's what AI is actually for.

00:01:48.440 --> 00:01:56.820
Not chatbots. Not image generators.
Matching the right resource to the right need
at the right time.

00:01:56.820 --> 00:02:00.160
It's called giving a shit.
Everyone eats.

